#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:42
# 963d61bfe4d74723965bd803ebf4fd60
msgid "JOSM has some additional tools to make it easier to draw lines and shapes. These tools are found in the :menuselection:`Tools` menu at the top of JOSM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:48
# 0b4a757fee964fce842247e7d89331cb
msgid "In order to apply the functions in this menu, you must first select a point, line or shape in the map window. Some of the most useful functions are described here:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:52
# 0ae26e4b9fbc4464a64ed3022a4011d3
msgid "**Split Way:** This allows you to divide a line into two separate lines. This is useful if you want to add different attributes to different parts of a road, such as a bridge. To use this function, select a point in the middle of the line that you want to split, Select :menuselection:`Split Way` from the :menuselection:`Tools` menu, and your line should be split in two."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:61
# 452eeb374b6d4afab95d4b3ef0190b9d
msgid "**Combine Way:** This does the opposite of :guilabel:`Split Way`. To combine two lines into a single line, they must share a single point. To use this function, select both lines that you want to combine. You can select more than one object by holding the :kbd:`SHIFT` key on your keyboard and clicking on each line. When you have selected both lines, select :menuselection:`Combine Way` from the :menuselection:`Tools` menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:71
# 4d0d87fcbea1435a80a855869bb9adfd
msgid "Note that you are combining roads that have different directions, you might get this warning:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:77
# 2449520c34cb46249bb7f87f25219207
msgid "If the roads are connected and go in the same direction, then choose :guilabel:`Reverse and Continue`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:80
# c0fb1778dbe44e6c8e7c338e0f1bfbee
msgid "**Reverse Way:** This will change the direction of the line. If the line incorrectly represents a road or river that is one way, you may want to change its direction. Unless someone has intentionally created a way to be one way you do not usually have to worry about altering the direction because ways in OSM default to both ways."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:89
# 0b72dcacd8354439b40faad51d15d785
msgid "**Simplify Way:** If your line has too many points in it and you’d like to make it simpler, this will remove some of the points from a line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:95
# 0290277d128945debee01054bad978bb
msgid "**Create Circle OR Align Nodes in Circle:** If you are trying to make a circular shape, draw the circle as best you can and then select three nodes and the function. It will help arrange your points in a circle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:105
# a95f9f6dee1843f2a726b941d8790f0d
msgid "**Align Nodes in Line:** This function will align a series of points into a"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:103
# ff327a26b0ca430497899ccef5865d4e
msgid "straight line. With long lines it is best to select sections of the line to straighten. Be careful as this does have the tendency to shift the line a little."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:110
# 62980a88f1234ddcad0ba7333d209f9f
msgid "**Orthogonalize Shape:** This function is very useful for drawing regular shapes such as buildings. After you draw an area, this function will reshape it to have square corners. This feature is most useful for other regularly shaped features, such as tennis courts, or landuse areas. (Using the :guilabel:`Building Plugin`, which will be explained below, might be easier)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:119
# cab3ff59786a46798f67f4877e97f8d5
msgid "**Unglue way:** This tools allows you to detach nodes that are connected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:124
# e758fa81cd3549a296fed72e4b56d44f
msgid "The line and node will not actually appear separate as the last screen shot implies."
msgstr ""

